Subject: [PATCH] libgloss: register libsysbase as a powerpc64-ps3-elf subdir

Adds libsysbase to libgloss's SUBDIRS for the PS3 target, matching the
pattern used by rs6000/mn10200/mips/etc.  Both the AC_CONFIG_FILES
registration (so the parent configure processes libsysbase/Makefile.in
→ Makefile via @var@ substitution) and the `subdirs` assignment (so
the parent make recurses in via automake's SUBDIRS machinery) are
needed.

Patches both configure.ac and the pre-generated configure script:
our build pipeline never runs autoreconf on libgloss, so configure.ac
changes alone don't reach the running configure.

diff --git a/libgloss/configure.ac b/libgloss/configure.ac
--- a/libgloss/configure.ac
+++ b/libgloss/configure.ac
@@ -114,6 +114,10 @@ case "${target}" in
 	subdirs="$subdirs rs6000"
 	host_makefile_frag=${srcdir}/config/ppc.mh
 	;;
+  powerpc64-ps3-elf*)
+	AC_CONFIG_FILES([libsysbase/Makefile])
+	subdirs="$subdirs libsysbase"
+	;;
   mn10200-*-*)
 	AC_CONFIG_FILES([mn10200/Makefile])
 	subdirs="$subdirs mn10200"
diff --git a/libgloss/configure b/libgloss/configure
--- a/libgloss/configure
+++ b/libgloss/configure
@@ -2839,6 +2839,11 @@ case "${target}" in
 	subdirs="$subdirs rs6000"
 	host_makefile_frag=${srcdir}/config/ppc.mh
 	;;
+  powerpc64-ps3-elf*)
+	ac_config_files="$ac_config_files libsysbase/Makefile"
+
+	subdirs="$subdirs libsysbase"
+	;;
   mn10200-*-*)
 	ac_config_files="$ac_config_files mn10200/Makefile"

